==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[μύθος]] (''mythos''), report, tale, story.

===Noun===
''mythos'' (''plural:'' '''[[mythoi]]''')

# A (fictional) history relevant to a particular character, group, or world. 
# Anything delivered by word of mouth, word, speech, conversation, story, tale, especially the poetic tale.    
# A tale, story or narrative, usually verbally transmitted, or recorded into the written from an alleged secondary source.

